================================================================================
DISCLAIMER
================================================================================

TachyGraph is an experimental, personal knowledge management system provided
"as is" without warranty of any kind. This software:

- May contain bugs, unhandled edge cases, and untested code paths
- Has not undergone formal security auditing or penetration testing
- Is not recommended for production use without thorough review
- Relies on third-party LLMs that may produce inaccurate, incomplete, or
  hallucinated outputs — always verify critical information independently
- Stores data locally in PostgreSQL with default credentials that must be
  changed before any non-local deployment
- Has features that may be partially complete or behave unexpectedly
  under certain conditions

The authors and contributors assume no responsibility for data loss,
security incidents, or incorrect information produced by this system.
Use at your own risk.

================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY ACKNOWLEDGMENTS
================================================================================

TachyGraph is built on the shoulders of the following open source projects.
We are deeply grateful to their authors and communities.

--- LLM INFERENCE & MODELS ---

Ollama
https://github.com/ollama/ollama
License: MIT
Local LLM inference server powering all generation and embedding calls.

Qwen3-Coder (30B) — by Alibaba Cloud / Qwen Team
https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3
License: Apache 2.0
Default generation model for summarization, fact extraction, disambiguation, and agent reasoning.

mxbai-embed-large — by Mixedbread AI
https://huggingface.co/mixedbread-ai/mxbai-embed-large-v1
License: Apache 2.0
Default embedding model producing 1024-dimensional vectors for semantic search.

--- DATABASE & VECTOR SEARCH ---

PostgreSQL
https://www.postgresql.org/
License: PostgreSQL License
Core relational database storing the knowledge graph, sessions, and all state.

pgvector — by Andrew Kane
https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector
License: PostgreSQL License
Vector similarity search extension for PostgreSQL, providing HNSW indexing and cosine distance operations.

pgvector-python — by Andrew Kane
https://github.com/pgvector/pgvector-python
License: MIT
Python client for pgvector, used for registering vector types with psycopg.

FAISS — by Meta AI Research
https://github.com/facebookresearch/faiss
License: MIT
High-performance vector similarity search library for CPU and GPU, used for accelerated approximate nearest neighbor retrieval.

--- WEB FRAMEWORK & NETWORKING ---

FastAPI — by Sebastián Ramírez
https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi
License: MIT
Async web framework powering all TachyGraph API endpoints.

Uvicorn
https://github.com/encode/uvicorn
License: BSD 3-Clause
ASGI server running the FastAPI application.

httpx
https://github.com/encode/httpx
License: BSD 3-Clause
HTTP client for Ollama API communication and web crawling.

--- AI AGENTS ---

Strands Agents SDK — by Amazon Web Services
https://github.com/strands-agents/sdk-python
License: Apache 2.0
Lightweight agent framework powering the single agent, orchestrator, researcher, and memory maintenance agents.

Model Context Protocol (MCP)
https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol
License: MIT
Protocol implementation for IDE integration (Claude Desktop, VS Code, Cursor).

--- PYTHON LIBRARIES ---

psycopg 3 — by Daniele Varrazzo
https://github.com/psycopg/psycopg
License: LGPL 3.0
PostgreSQL adapter for Python, providing connection pooling and async support.

NumPy
https://github.com/numpy/numpy
License: BSD 3-Clause
Numerical computing library used for vector normalization and FAISS interop.

LangChain Text Splitters
https://github.com/langchain-ai/langchain
License: MIT
Markdown and recursive character text splitting for document chunking.

APScheduler
https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler
License: MIT
Background task scheduler for MMR recomputation and maintenance cron jobs.

BeautifulSoup 4 — by Leonard Richardson
https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/
License: MIT
HTML parsing for the local web scraper fallback.

html2text — by Aaron Swartz (original), Alireza Savand (maintainer)
https://github.com/Alir3z4/html2text
License: GPL-3.0-only
HTML to Markdown conversion for web crawl ingestion.

PyMuPDF (fitz)
https://github.com/pymupdf/PyMuPDF
License: AGPL 3.0 / Commercial
PDF text extraction for local file ingestion.

Pydantic — by Samuel Colvin
https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic
License: MIT
Data validation for all FastAPI request/response models.

--- INFRASTRUCTURE ---

Docker & Docker Compose
https://github.com/docker
License: Apache 2.0
Containerization and orchestration for the full stack.

Python 3.11
https://www.python.org/
License: PSF License
Runtime language for the entire application.

--- OPTIONAL DEPENDENCIES ---

faster-whisper (optional)
https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper
License: MIT
Audio transcription for mp3/wav/m4a ingestion when enabled.

Cloudflare Browser Rendering API (optional, untested)
https://developers.cloudflare.com/browser-rendering/
Hosted browser automation service for rendering JavaScript-heavy pages and extracting content; falls back to the local scraper (httpx + BeautifulSoup) by default.

--- SAMPLE DATA ---

"A deep learning framework for jointly solving transient Fokker-Planck
equations with arbitrary parameters and initial distributions"
  Authors: Xiaolong Wang, Jing Feng, Qi Liu, Chengli Tan, Yuanyuan Liu, Yong Xu
  Institutions: Shaanxi Normal University, Northwestern Polytechnical University,
                Xi'an University of Posts and Telecommunications,
                Institute of Science Tokyo
  arXiv: 2604.06001v1 [physics.comp-ph]
  Used as sample text content for testing the ingestion pipeline.
  This paper is included solely for demonstration purposes and remains the
  intellectual property of its authors. All rights belong to the original authors.

"Statistical description of dust polarized emission from the diffuse
interstellar medium using RWST approach"
  Used as sample web content for testing the web crawl ingestion pipeline.
  This paper is included solely for demonstration purposes and remains the
  intellectual property of its authors. All rights belong to the original authors.

